Measure type: [730] Compliance with the pre-export checks requirements
[730] Compliance with the pre-export checks requirements
[730] Compliance with the pre-export checks requirements
Conditions: TM774: (Taric Measure) The frequency of physical checks carried out by the Member States shall be reduced to a maximum of 1% of consignments provided the consignments are accompanied by the following documents: (a) a report containing the results of sampling and analysis performed in accordance with the provisions of Commission Regulation (EC) No 401/2006 of 23 February 2006 laying down the methods of sampling and analysis for the official control of mycotoxins in foodstuffs, or with equivalent requirements, by a laboratory approved for that purpose by the Canadian Grain Commission (TARIC certificate code C685);  (b) a certificate in accordance with the model set out in the Annex II of R 2015/949, completed, verified and signed by a representative of the Canadian Grain Commission; the certificate shall be valid for four months from the date of issuance (TARIC certificate code C684).
